## Motivation

Exploitable vulnerabilities at the code level remain a major risk to all blockchain ecosystems. Providing continuous AI-native secure code tooling to 30 ecosystem teams establishes stronger security practices while lowering the cost of maintaining them.

This initiative:

- Improves developer safety  
- Reduces deployment risk  
- Increases institutional confidence  

This model mirrors successful ecosystem security programs in other blockchain ecosystems and represents a practical path to improving security standards across Canton Network.
---

## Rationale

Shared security infrastructure is the most scalable way to improve ecosystem wide security.

Implementing Almanax within the Canton ecosystem provides:

- Consistent security capabilities across projects and access to security tooling for early stage teams  
- Continuous monitoring instead of one off audits  
- Faster remediation and improved developer productivity
